Part I - (FordGoBike Data Analysis)¶

by (Okeri Mwikali Josephine)¶

Introduction¶

This data set consist of 183 000 rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area. The dataset include the following features rider duration, Stations, time, gender of the rider and also user type.

Issue 4. The start_time and end_time contain hour, day and month information¶

Define. Extract Hour, day and month from the start_time and End_time¶

Code¶

In [11]:
import datetime as dt
df_bike_clean['start_hour']=df_bike_clean['start_time'].dt.hour
df_bike_clean.start_hour=df_bike_clean.start_hour.astype(str)
df_bike_clean['start_day']=df_bike_clean['start_time'].dt.day_name()
df_bike_clean['start_month']=df_bike_clean['start_time'].dt.month_name()

df_bike_clean['end_hour']=df_bike_clean['end_time'].dt.hour
df_bike_clean.end_hour=df_bike_clean.end_hour.astype(str)
df_bike_clean['end_day']=df_bike_clean['end_time'].dt.day_name()
df_bike_clean['end_month']=df_bike_clean['end_time'].dt.month_name()

def myplot(x,y,t):
    """
    arg:
    x:x-axis
    y:y_axis
    t:graph title
    Return:
    None
    """
    plt.xlabel(x)
    plt.ylabel(y)
    plt.title(t)
    color=sb.color_palette()[2]
    plt.show()

In [23]:
# convert day, and hour into categorical types
day_hour_class = {'start_day': ['Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday'],
                    'end_day': ['Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday'],
                   'start_hour': [str(i) for i in range(0,24)],
                   'end_hour': [str(i) for i in range(0,24)]}

for var in day_hour_class:
    dhclass = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(ordered = True, categories = day_hour_class[var])
    df_bike_clean[var] = df_bike_clean[var].astype(dhclass)

Conclusions¶

From the findings:

  • most subscribers rent bike for short distances compared to the customers who take for long trips.
  • Most males rides bike with higher percentage than female and the other
  • Most males recorded high bike share
  • most hours that are not that busy that when we have bike share and least recording at busy hours
  • Weekends have long duration trips compared to the week days
  • The other gender that share bike most were born between 1982 and 1984
  • Most trips are on weekdays and thursday having the high number of trips. On weekends trip are low(saturday and sunday)
  • Most of the riders are the subscriber.
  • Most rides are at rush hours between 8th, 9th and 17th,18th
  • Only subscibers are allowed to share bike
  • customers travel long distances each day compared to subscribers
  • Most subscribers are male
  • Most young people born in 1980s and below ride bike for longers duration.
  • There is strong relationship between young people born on 1970 up to 2000 for subscribers compared to customers
